## Architectural Concerns
- Algebraic component tests are structurally weak; they verify rendering without crashing but don't validate pedagogical behavior (step progression, distractor interaction, hint system)
- `content-hash.ts` uses Node.js `crypto` which runs in V8 runtime for queries/mutations ‚Äî works today because Convex V8 has polyfills but could break with runtime changes
- No auth checks in `convex/dev.ts` ‚Äî internal functions rely on callers for access control (Phase 3 will add developer-only guards)
